<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><!DOCTYPE article  PUBLIC '-//OASIS//DTD DocBook XML V4.4//EN'  'http://www.docbook.org/xml/4.4/docbookx.dtd'><article><articleinfo><title>Features/MemcachedStoreDir</title><revhistory><revision><revnumber>2</revnumber><date>2015-09-21 05:16:33</date><authorinitials>AmosJeffries</authorinitials></revision><revision><revnumber>1</revnumber><date>2009-10-03 13:04:05</date><authorinitials>FrancescoChemolli</authorinitials></revision></revhistory></articleinfo><section><title>Feature: memcached-based storedir</title><itemizedlist><listitem><para><emphasis role="strong">Goal</emphasis>: Implement a memcached-based storedir for out-of-process cache handling </para></listitem><listitem><para><emphasis role="strong">Status</emphasis>: not started </para></listitem></itemizedlist><itemizedlist><listitem><para><emphasis role="strong">ETA</emphasis>: unknown </para></listitem><listitem><para><emphasis role="strong">Version</emphasis>:  </para></listitem><listitem><para><emphasis role="strong">Developer</emphasis>: <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/Features/MemcachedStoreDir/FrancescoChemolli#">FrancescoChemolli</ulink> </para></listitem><listitem><para><emphasis role="strong">More</emphasis>:  </para></listitem></itemizedlist></section><section><title>Details</title><para><ulink url="http://www.danga.com/memcached/">Memcached</ulink> is a popular mechanism for storing out-of-process RAM-based caches, in some cases (e.g. facebook) of huge proportions. It would make sense to create an asyncrhonous storedir which talks to one or more memcached-based backends for storing contents, possibly using selectors a la <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/Features/MemcachedStoreDir/Features/CyclicObjectStorageSystem#">COSS</ulink> to maximize the performance gains. </para><!--rule (<hr>) is not applicable to DocBook--><para> <ulink url="https://wiki.squid-cache.org/Features/MemcachedStoreDir/CategoryFeature#">CategoryFeature</ulink> </para></section></article>